#Text=County Limerick

#Text=County Limerick ( Irish : Contae Luimnigh ) is the smallest and least scenic county in Ireland 's Shannon Region , but it contains Ireland 's third largest city and the island 's largest river .
#Text=It is more likely to be on your route than your destination but there are things worth seeing .
#Text=Towns
#Text=( Luimneach ) is the only city in the county .
#Text=It has many sights and facilities and is the obvious base for exploring the area plus nearby County Clare .
#Text=( Áth Dara ) is a picturesque ( and frankly touristy ) village with Castle Desmond , a couple of abbeys and a plush manor hotel .
#Text=( an Caisleán Nua Thiar ) is a town further west with another Castle Desmond .
#Text=( Eas Géitine ) is a small town near the Shannon with , guess what , Castle Desmond .
#Text=( The Earls of Desmond built castles in other counties which for some reason they gave different names . )
#Text=A little further west is Foynes with the flying boat museum .
#Text=( An Brú ) is the closest settlement to Lough Gur which has prehistoric remains .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Limerick is located in the province of Munster .
#Text=It is named after the city of Limerick which has an urban population of about 100,000 people .
#Text=Limerick is the tenth largest of Ireland ’s 32 counties by area and the eighth largest by population .
#Text=It is the fifth largest of Munster ’s 6 counties in size and the second largest by population .
#Text=The River Shannon flows through the city of Limerick into the Atlantic Ocean at the north of the county .
#Text=Below the city , the waterway is known as the Shannon Estuary .
#Text=Because the estuary is shallow , the county 's most important port is several kilometres west of the city , at Foynes .
#Text=Newcastle West is the most important county town outside of Limerick city with a population of around 10,000 .
#Text=Other towns mainly lie along the Limerick – Tralee roads ( N21 ) and Limerick – Cork road ( N20 ) .
#Text=Get in
#Text=By plane :
#Text=The closest is 24 km west of Limerick in County Clare , with flights across Europe & UK and to the United States .
#Text=It does n't have flights within Ireland .
#Text=Dublin Airport ( DUB ) has a wider selection of flights and is served by the X12 bus direct to Limerick , 3 hr 30 min .
#Text=By train :
#Text=The only railway station in the county is Limerick Colbert .
#Text=This has hourly trains from Dublin Heuston , some direct but mostly with a change at Limerick Junction which is near Tipperary ; and change here for Cork .
#Text=Trains also run from Limerick to Ennis and Galway .
#Text=By car : the main roads all converge on Limerick .
#Text=From Dublin , N7 is all motorway once you get past Naas , 200 km or 3 hours in all .
#Text=Other major routes are N18 / M18 to Shannon Airport , Ennis and Galway , N20 to Mallow and Cork , N21 to Tralee and Killarney , and N24 to Tipperary and Waterford .
#Text=By bus : Bus Eireann X12 runs hourly to Nenagh , Roscrea , Portlaoise , Dublin Busáras ( 3 hours ) and Dublin Airport .
#Text=Bus 51 runs hourly across the county from Cork and Mallow to Limerick , continuing north via Shannon Airport and Ennis to Galway .
#Text=There are also buses every few hours from Limerick to Tralee , Killarney , Waterford and Athlone .
#Text=Car Rental
#Text=The main location for picking up a car rental in County Limerick is at Shannon International Airport .
#Text=See
#Text=Limerick is an elegant Georgian city with a castle and two cathedrals .
#Text=Adare is an attractive small town with thatched cottages and a stout castle .
#Text=It 's mobbed with tourists at the height of summer .
#Text=Newcastle West along N21 towards Tralee has the 15th C Castle Desmond , open May-Aug daily .
#Text=( Not to be confused with the similarly named castle in Adare . )
#Text=Eat
#Text=Limerick City has some of the best restaurants in Ireland , see city listings .
#Text=Drink
#Text=Tom Collins Oyster bar , Cecil St. ( just off O'Connell Street in the city center ) .
#Text=fine example of an old style irish pub , popular with locals .
#Text=The Strand Hotel bar , Sarsfield Bridge .
#Text=Popular with both home and visiting fans before and after a match at Thomand park .
#Text=Those without tickets can watch the match on several large screen TVs .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Old Bank B&B , in Bruff near Lough Gur .
